    <h3 class="title"><a href="/terminal-mode-or-standard-mounting-port-mobile-phones-cars#comment-12820" class="active">Not strong enough</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Fri, 2011-05-06 14:56.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>The micro usb is never going to do it, in a car you need something to handle the bumps and hold something as heavy as a tablet.</p>

<p>And yes, wired data should always be there if it can be.  Wireless data is getting better, but the open bands are getting noisy and you have to do pairing.</p>
